1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:06,840
- Okay.
- One!

2
00:00:06,923 --> 00:00:09,217
- One!
- Close. Ready, and two! Shit!

3
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:10,635
- Right, ready.
- Let's go again.

4
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:11,594
- Zero!
- [groans]

5
00:00:11,678 --> 00:00:12,929
Yeah!

6
00:00:13,638 --> 00:00:15,390
That's it, I win. Pay up.

7
00:00:15,890 --> 00:00:17,934
- Let's go again.
- I already beat you. No.

8
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:20,603
- Double or nothing, man!
- [resident 1] No, I'm done!

9
00:00:20,687 --> 00:00:23,440
[resident 2] Come on, one more.
Don't tell me you're chicken?

10
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:25,316
[resident 1] I know I can beat you.

11
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:27,402
[ominous music droning]

12
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:36,036
I got four today.

13
00:00:37,412 --> 00:00:40,582
You sure you wanna do it like this?
It's the only way?

14
00:00:40,665 --> 00:00:43,126
[man sighs] There's no problem,
all right? Look.

15
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:45,045
We've already reinforced the tunnel…

16
00:00:45,128 --> 00:00:46,421
METEORITE IMPACT POINT

17
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:50,383
…right under the meteorite.
We place the bomb here, and we blow it up.

18
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:51,801
It'll collapse the whole cave

19
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:55,221
and the meteorite will end up
buried deep underground.

20
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:56,765
I told you, no problem.

21
00:00:57,265 --> 00:00:59,350
Doesn't sound like no problem. Come on!

22
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:02,228
Do you understand
how many people we've already lost?

23
00:01:02,312 --> 00:01:04,105
Hey, relax. No one cares.

24
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:06,149
Let's get this done
and keep our mouths shut.

25
00:01:06,232 --> 00:01:08,276
They want more people,
I'll bring 'em more.

26
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:09,944
[Obata] How can you talk like that?

27
00:01:10,445 --> 00:01:11,696
Don't walk away!

28
00:01:12,197 --> 00:01:14,657
Our orders are coming from the very top.

29
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:18,369
Do us all a favor
and keep your personal views to yourself.

30
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:20,914
We've got a job to do, so get to work.

31
00:01:22,791 --> 00:01:23,917
[Obata] Damn it.

32
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:26,419
I can't believe this.

33
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:28,505
[ominous music building]

34
00:01:40,308 --> 00:01:42,727
- [man 1] Okay, everyone, put these on.
- [music fades out]

35
00:01:42,811 --> 00:01:44,562
CHILDREN OF THE WORLD PEACE EXPO '99

36
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:48,650
[man 2] Come on, put the masks on.

37
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:51,486
Hurry. Don't make me tell you
a second time.

38
00:01:51,569 --> 00:01:53,947
Walk for about half a mile,
then you'll reach a cave.

39
00:01:54,030 --> 00:01:56,950
You'll see the meteorite from there.
The job's simple.

40
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:59,744
All you have to do
is leave this at the cave entrance.

41
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:01,079
A monkey could do it.

42
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:02,622
Easy.

43
00:02:09,712 --> 00:02:10,797
Hey!

44
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:16,386
If you do this, and you do it right,
you're going to walk away filthy rich.

45
00:02:16,469 --> 00:02:18,054
Tell me that doesn't appeal to you.

46
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:20,014
Just get it done.

47
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:21,850
[man 1] All right, everyone!

48
00:02:25,103 --> 00:02:27,272
[resident 1] Okay, I'm going in first.

49
00:02:27,355 --> 00:02:30,150
[resident 2] Always hogging the glory,
aren't you, Shortstack?

50
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:34,112
[resident 1] Only 'cause you're too busy
pissing your pants in fear.

51
00:02:34,195 --> 00:02:37,532
[man 1] All right, stop squabbling
and be careful with the thing!

52
00:02:37,615 --> 00:02:39,576
- [Ren] You okay?
- [resident 3] Yeah.

53
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:42,579
[man 2] Hey. Stop slacking
and get yours on too.

54
00:02:44,247 --> 00:02:47,208
You wouldn't want the little princess
to worry, would you?

55
00:02:51,462 --> 00:02:53,840
[man 1] Can you handle that?
It's pretty heavy.

56
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:57,010
- Good luck in there!
- [resident 3 grunts]

57
00:02:57,093 --> 00:03:00,305
- [man 1] Watch where you step.
- [man 2] Make sure they don't try to run.

58
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:03,433
WATCH OUT FOR FORK IN THE ROAD!

59
00:03:03,516 --> 00:03:05,768
3/8 ARRIVAL AT IMPACT POINT

60
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,854
[exhausted groaning]

61
00:03:07,937 --> 00:03:09,606
[chilling music playing]

62
00:03:09,689 --> 00:03:11,983
[resident groaning wearily]

63
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:15,361
[Ren breathing anxiously]

64
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:17,447
[resident gasping, wheezing]

65
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:43,598
[crunching underfoot]

66
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:49,812
[Ren whimpering]

67
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:51,773
[gasping]

68
00:03:58,446 --> 00:04:00,448
[panicked breathing]

69
00:04:08,456 --> 00:04:09,707
[wheezing]

70
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:11,918
[music becomes sinister]

71
00:04:21,636 --> 00:04:23,763
[shattering, crumbling]

72
00:04:23,846 --> 00:04:26,266
[Ren breathing raggedly]

73
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:32,272
[gagging, coughing]

74
00:04:55,753 --> 00:04:57,755
[Ren panting]

75
00:05:09,183 --> 00:05:11,185
[gasping]

76
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:13,604
[unsettling pulsating, high-pitched tone]

77
00:05:17,775 --> 00:05:20,153
[pulsating tone becoming stronger]

78
00:05:27,076 --> 00:05:28,703
[Ren wheezes]

79
00:05:32,206 --> 00:05:33,916
[panicked breathing]

80
00:05:36,252 --> 00:05:37,170
[grunting]

81
00:05:39,672 --> 00:05:42,008
[choking]

82
00:05:44,218 --> 00:05:46,888
[Ren screaming]

83
00:05:49,057 --> 00:05:50,350
[klaxon blares]

84
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:53,728
- What?
- [klaxon blares]

85
00:05:53,811 --> 00:05:55,938
Wait, don't tell me they actually…

86
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:57,774
There is no way…

87
00:05:57,857 --> 00:06:00,109
It's happening! We're finally done!

88
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:01,194
[yells excitedly]

89
00:06:01,277 --> 00:06:03,446
Okay, let's blow it up! Let's go! Hit it!

90
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:04,655
No, no, no, we can't!

91
00:06:04,739 --> 00:06:07,492
There's still people in there.
You'll kill them! Don't do it!

92
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:13,706
- [shouting outside]
- [frantic, tense music playing]

93
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:17,126
[man, outside] Do it, goddammit!

94
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:18,711
[Sano hesitating]

95
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:21,714
Uh?

96
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,970
- [rapid footsteps]
- [Ren choking]

97
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,640
[panting]

98
00:06:31,682 --> 00:06:34,435
[tense, dramatic music playing]

99
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:41,776
- [Obata] No, don't do it!
- Hey, look! Look!

100
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:45,530
[Ren gasping, choking]

101
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:49,158
[man grunting]

102
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:52,912
- [Ren choking]
- [man grunting]

103
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:56,082
Get the hell off me!

104
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:59,210
[Ren groaning]

105
00:07:01,295 --> 00:07:02,630
[pained yelling]

106
00:07:05,883 --> 00:07:08,970
Help me! [screaming]

107
00:07:21,065 --> 00:07:22,400
[Sano] Just fucking do it.

108
00:07:26,195 --> 00:07:28,614
[Ren screaming]

109
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:31,617
[explosion echoing]

110
00:07:36,956 --> 00:07:39,459
[dark, dramatic music playing]

111
00:08:16,037 --> 00:08:21,250
HUMAN VAPOR

112
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:24,086
<i>The body of Police</i>
<i>Superintendent General Sakamoto</i>

113
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:27,840
<i>has been located by police</i>
<i>in a parked car in Minato Ward.</i>

114
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:29,550
<i>Ms. Araki is live now.</i>

115
00:08:30,676 --> 00:08:33,346
<i>Just behind me is the site</i>
<i>of the gruesome discovery</i>

116
00:08:33,429 --> 00:08:34,555
<i>earlier tonight.</i>

117
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:35,932
[concerned chattering]

118
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:38,643
[Araki] <i>Superintendent General Sakamoto</i>
<i>was found dead</i>

119
00:08:38,726 --> 00:08:41,312
<i>in the black car</i>
<i>you can see just behind me.</i>

120
00:08:41,395 --> 00:08:43,189
<i>Police have cordoned off the scene.</i>

121
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:45,691
<i>Just hours before the body was found,</i>

122
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:49,070
<i>the Human Vapor had announced</i>
<i>his intention to kill Sakamoto</i>

123
00:08:49,153 --> 00:08:51,364
<i>via a live stream channel</i>…

124
00:08:51,447 --> 00:08:52,698
[phone ringing out]

125
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:54,408
KAHO, TERROR ZONE

126
00:08:54,492 --> 00:08:55,618
[phone ringing out]

127
00:08:55,701 --> 00:08:57,245
[Kyoko sighs]

128
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:06,379
"Kaho, has anything happened?
Are you okay? Call me."

129
00:09:08,422 --> 00:09:09,590
[phone buzzes]

130
00:09:10,299 --> 00:09:12,218
"I'm fine, call you later."

131
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:14,220
- [Kaho grunting]
- [man 1] Stop it! Come on!

132
00:09:14,303 --> 00:09:16,806
- [man 2] Hold still, damn it!
- [Kaho] Give me my phone!

133
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:18,432
[man 1] Shut up, shut up!

134
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:19,809
Ah! She bit me, what the fuck?!

135
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:21,519
- Get over here!
- Hey!

136
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:22,645
Tie her up, quick!

137
00:09:23,187 --> 00:09:25,648
- [Riki] Like you should've done first!
- Sorry, Riki.

138
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:28,818
- [man 3] Stop making trouble, got it?
- [Kaho] Let go of me!

139
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:31,821
[Riki] We just wanna know who this is.
Who sent you this message?

140
00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:33,364
[man 3] Answer the boss, now!

141
00:09:33,447 --> 00:09:35,658
So, Okamoto…

142
00:09:38,286 --> 00:09:41,455
What did you talk about
with the superintendent general?

143
00:09:46,335 --> 00:09:47,670
What, you deaf now?

144
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:55,219
We need to know what the man said to you
right before he killed himself.

145
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:58,723
- Killed himself?
- Yeah.

146
00:09:59,515 --> 00:10:01,726
After the Human Vapor's video.

147
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:06,105
No wonder he felt there was no way out.

148
00:10:09,317 --> 00:10:10,901
You did it! It was you!

149
00:10:10,985 --> 00:10:13,487
You killed him,
and you made it look like a suicide!

150
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:15,990
- Didn't you? Didn't you?!
- [Michiko] Let him go!

151
00:10:16,073 --> 00:10:18,409
- Fuckin' crazy!
- [Michiko] Let him go, damn it!

152
00:10:18,492 --> 00:10:20,369
[chief] Are you out of your goddamn mind?

153
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:21,746
[Kenji panting]

154
00:10:21,829 --> 00:10:23,205
What's wrong with you?

155
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:26,500
One more step out of line,
and you're outta here.

156
00:10:26,584 --> 00:10:29,045
Yoshida's just trying
to figure out what happened.

157
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:33,549
We've got nothing to go on.
No cameras at the crime scene.

158
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,510
And because of that, we…

159
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:40,056
Without better evidence,
we have to treat this as suicide.

160
00:10:40,973 --> 00:10:43,476
[Kenji breathes heavily]

161
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:52,693
[Kenji sighs]

162
00:10:54,737 --> 00:10:56,656
The last thing the man said

163
00:10:58,449 --> 00:11:01,243
was that we should all go out
for dinner again.

164
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:02,787
That's all he said.

165
00:11:04,288 --> 00:11:05,247
[sighs]

166
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:09,377
There was a sadness behind his eyes.

167
00:11:09,877 --> 00:11:13,005
They looked like the eyes of a man
who was going to take his own life.

168
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:16,717
That good enough for you?

169
00:11:19,136 --> 00:11:21,097
That's real cute, Detective.

170
00:11:21,681 --> 00:11:24,600
[chief] He's a loose cannon.
We gotta rein him in.

171
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,646
[tense music playing]

172
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:39,156
[doors unlocking]

173
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,783
[footsteps approaching]

174
00:11:40,866 --> 00:11:43,119
[breathing heavily]

175
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:47,498
[melancholy music playing]

176
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:48,666
[bangs fist]

177
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:51,877
[exhales]

178
00:12:12,356 --> 00:12:13,399
[Sakamoto] <i>Kenji.</i>

179
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,695
<i>There's something else you should know.</i>

180
00:12:18,738 --> 00:12:20,030
<i>Your father…</i>

181
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:23,743
<i>I'm responsible for his death.</i>

182
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:36,255
[Chieko] <i>My husband had</i>
<i>a strong sense of justice.</i>

183
00:12:36,338 --> 00:12:39,675
<i>- I hope he'll be remembered for that.</i>
- [reporter 1] <i>Did you find documents…</i>

184
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:41,969
[Tatsuya] It's awful,
putting her through this.

185
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,555
I mean, he just died.

186
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:46,849
[reporter 2] <i>Do you think</i>
<i>the threat led to his suicide?</i>

187
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:49,351
[Tatsuya] No wonder people hate the media.

188
00:12:50,227 --> 00:12:52,104
Here. You should eat something.

189
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:55,149
[reporter 3]
<i>Did he get along with colleagues?</i>

190
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:57,818
It seemed like the two of them
were really in love.

191
00:12:59,361 --> 00:13:00,905
Apparently they met at school.

192
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:03,491
[reporter 4] <i>Did he tell you</i>
<i>anything pertaining to the case?</i>

193
00:13:03,574 --> 00:13:06,786
<i>- Was your husband afraid?</i>
<i>- Was there really no suicide note?</i>

194
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:08,954
[reporters all speak at once]

195
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:12,208
Whoa, what's wrong?

196
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:15,836
- [Chieko] <i>Nothing else was found.</i>
- [reporter 5] <i>Has a search been done?</i>

197
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:18,047
[reporters continue questioning]

198
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:19,632
I'm going out for a bit.

199
00:13:19,715 --> 00:13:21,091
Oh, okay.

200
00:13:44,114 --> 00:13:45,115
Oh-ho!

201
00:13:45,199 --> 00:13:46,283
Oh…

202
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:48,077
Sh…

203
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,328
4.01 MILLION VIEWS

204
00:13:49,912 --> 00:13:51,997
[gasping]

205
00:13:52,081 --> 00:13:54,083
[calm music playing]

206
00:13:57,586 --> 00:13:59,588
[music fades out]

207
00:14:08,722 --> 00:14:09,682
Kaho!

208
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:12,935
It's a great day for believers!

209
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:14,645
Guess what?

210
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:17,731
I scored four unsold bento boxes!

211
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:22,027
Kaho?

212
00:14:23,279 --> 00:14:24,363
Kaho?

213
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:27,032
- [Kaho whimpers]
- Hey, buddy.

214
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:29,535
- [dramatic music playing]
- [grunting]

215
00:14:29,618 --> 00:14:30,536
Kaho!

216
00:14:30,619 --> 00:14:32,621
[men grunting]

217
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:38,043
- [man 1] Stop!
- [Fujita] Kaho!

218
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:40,254
- [man 2] You're making it worse!
- [Kaho yelling]

219
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:42,715
[man 1] Hey!

220
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:46,635
[grunting]

221
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:50,973
- [man 1] Hey!
- [man 2] Come back!

222
00:14:51,056 --> 00:14:52,766
- [man 3] Shit!
- [man 2] You little--

223
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:54,393
[man 1] I'm gonna kick your ass!

224
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:56,353
[Fujita grunting]

225
00:14:56,437 --> 00:14:57,438
[man 1 yells]

226
00:14:58,606 --> 00:14:59,690
[Fujita] Kaho!

227
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:01,066
[Kaho whimpering]

228
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:03,152
- I got you. I got you!
- [Riki] Fujita!

229
00:15:03,235 --> 00:15:04,570
[Kaho screaming]

230
00:15:04,653 --> 00:15:05,571
[Fujita groans]

231
00:15:06,155 --> 00:15:07,865
- [Riki] And stay down!
- [Kaho squeals]

232
00:15:07,948 --> 00:15:08,991
[Fujita grunts]

233
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:10,075
[groaning]

234
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:13,162
[Riki] Both so stubborn.
No wonder you're brother and sister.

235
00:15:13,662 --> 00:15:15,623
A waste of our precious time.

236
00:15:16,582 --> 00:15:18,500
- Tie him up.
- [man 2] Yes, sir.

237
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:19,877
[Kaho whimpering]

238
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,754
[Riki] And you, shut up.

239
00:15:23,005 --> 00:15:25,007
[music fades out]

240
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:36,352
COMMENDATION
ASSISTANT INSPECTOR SHINYA OKAMOTO

241
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:47,488
[mournful music playing]

242
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:50,407
[sighs sadly]

243
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:58,749
CHILDREN OF THE WORLD PEACE EXPO '99

244
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:03,045
[Sakamoto] Listen.

245
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:06,632
I know all about
your current investigation.

246
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:10,302
[Shinya] What are you trying to say?

247
00:16:10,386 --> 00:16:11,845
[music fades out]

248
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:13,555
Just that… [sighs]

249
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:18,018
[Shinya sniffs]

250
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:22,564
…it runs deeper than you think.
Trust me, I know.

251
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:31,490
[Shinya] Hmm.

252
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:35,077
What do you mean,

253
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:37,121
you know?

254
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:42,126
[Sakamoto]
You're investigating that facility,

255
00:16:42,209 --> 00:16:44,461
and you've uncovered things
better left buried.

256
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:46,880
And now you're after that yakuza too.

257
00:16:48,590 --> 00:16:50,342
Does that mean you know

258
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:53,887
what they're doing to people
at that center?

259
00:17:01,437 --> 00:17:02,730
[Sakamoto sighs]

260
00:17:03,856 --> 00:17:04,815
Yeah.

261
00:17:06,358 --> 00:17:09,445
All I'm saying… is just stay out of it.

262
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:11,572
[Shinya breathes deeply]

263
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,200
Stay out of it?

264
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:19,621
Sakamoto,

265
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:23,333
do you have any idea
what you're asking me to do?

266
00:17:24,168 --> 00:17:26,962
[Sakamoto] <i>Do </i>you <i>have any idea</i>
<i>who these people are?</i>

267
00:17:27,755 --> 00:17:29,339
<i>These aren't just criminals.</i>

268
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:32,092
If you know their names,

269
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:33,927
you already know too much.

270
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:35,387
So I just back off?

271
00:17:37,556 --> 00:17:39,558
No matter who we're facing down,

272
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:44,271
it's our job and our responsibility
to uncover the truth, no matter the cost.

273
00:17:44,354 --> 00:17:45,522
Am I wrong?

274
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:47,608
[doleful music playing]

275
00:17:49,818 --> 00:17:50,736
[Shinya sighs]

276
00:17:55,741 --> 00:17:57,076
Give us a minute, Kenji.

277
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:01,080
[door closing]

278
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:03,874
[Kenji breathing anxiously]

279
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:05,959
[Kenji] What happened to my dad?

280
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:09,338
[Sakamoto] He was chasing
a fleeing suspect.

281
00:18:10,339 --> 00:18:12,716
A truck came out of nowhere and hit him.

282
00:18:14,968 --> 00:18:15,928
Dad?

283
00:18:17,429 --> 00:18:18,347
Dad?

284
00:18:19,306 --> 00:18:20,182
Come on!

285
00:18:21,308 --> 00:18:22,434
Dad, wake up!

286
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:24,645
Please…

287
00:18:26,021 --> 00:18:28,023
[music becomes mysterious]

288
00:18:53,465 --> 00:18:57,803
ABOUT WHITE CENTER:
IT PROVIDES JOBS TO PEOPLE IN NEED

289
00:19:06,353 --> 00:19:09,273
YASUTOSHI MORI PHYSICAL FEATURES:
SNAKE TATTOO ON WRIST

290
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:12,359
[Mori] <i>I knew an Okamoto once.</i>
<i>What are you, his son?</i>

291
00:19:12,442 --> 00:19:16,572
<i>The two of us, we go way back,</i>
<i>your old man and I.</i>

292
00:19:16,655 --> 00:19:19,950
No, he wasn't so smart in the end.

293
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:21,785
Such a tragedy.

294
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:23,036
[croaks]

295
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:25,122
[tense music playing]

296
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:28,167
[dramatic drumbeats pounding]

297
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:34,381
[music fades out]

298
00:19:34,464 --> 00:19:36,550
[man 1] Start talking, nerd boy!

299
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:38,260
You brought this on yourself!

300
00:19:38,343 --> 00:19:41,430
Now you know what happens
when you keep your mouth shut!

301
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:42,848
You know I could kill you!

302
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:43,974
[Fujita gasping]

303
00:19:44,057 --> 00:19:44,933
[man 1] Come on!

304
00:19:45,517 --> 00:19:48,061
- Ka… Kaho! Kaho!
- [Riki] Fujita…

305
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:51,106
- [Fujita] Get away from her!
- Should I cut off your sister's mark?

306
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:53,400
I could do it so nice and clean
with my knife.

307
00:19:53,483 --> 00:19:57,696
No, no, no! Leave her alone!
You piece of shit!

308
00:19:57,779 --> 00:19:58,947
[Riki] Look, my friend,

309
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:02,993
if you'll just tell us what we wanna know,

310
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:06,538
I'll let both of you walk free,
simple as that.

311
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:08,874
- Okay?
- [Fujita panting]

312
00:20:08,957 --> 00:20:11,418
- [Kaho] Fujita!
- How'd you get this video?

313
00:20:11,501 --> 00:20:14,546
Why did the Human Vapor
send it to you, huh?

314
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:17,257
Don't tell him anything, Fujita!

315
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:19,384
[suspenseful music playing]

316
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:22,262
Please! Don't do it!

317
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:24,932
- Well?
- The Human Vapor…

318
00:20:25,015 --> 00:20:27,392
- Yeah…
- [Kaho] No! Stop!

319
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:29,478
It's possible to control him.

320
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:30,729
Fujita!

321
00:20:30,812 --> 00:20:32,481
[whimpering]

322
00:20:32,564 --> 00:20:34,983
[Fujita] I gave an order
to the Human Vapor.

323
00:20:36,526 --> 00:20:38,695
I was the one who took the video.

324
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:44,076
[Riki laughing]

325
00:20:44,159 --> 00:20:47,079
"Gave an order"? Show me how you did it.

326
00:20:49,373 --> 00:20:51,375
[music stops]

327
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:17,943
EVIDENCE STORAGE ROOM 5

328
00:21:18,026 --> 00:21:19,111
Through here.

329
00:21:20,362 --> 00:21:21,196
Thanks.

330
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:28,662
[determined music playing]

331
00:21:42,509 --> 00:21:44,845
"Yasutoshi Mori, aged 54."

332
00:21:44,928 --> 00:21:47,222
"Ligature on neck from bathrobe belt."

333
00:21:50,142 --> 00:21:53,562
"Minor chemical burns present
in both lungs."

334
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:59,234
[Michiko] <i>Kyugo Sano,</i>
<i>professor of environmental engineering.</i>

335
00:21:59,735 --> 00:22:02,779
<i>There were severe thermal injuries</i>
<i>on the inner lung tissue,</i>

336
00:22:02,863 --> 00:22:04,448
<i>more consistent with chemical burns</i>

337
00:22:04,531 --> 00:22:07,451
<i>than those typically caused</i>
<i>by high temperatures.</i>

338
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:15,334
[Kenji] "Fujishiro Syndicate members."

339
00:22:18,211 --> 00:22:20,172
Saburo Otomo.

340
00:22:20,255 --> 00:22:21,757
Riki Otomo.

341
00:22:22,257 --> 00:22:23,425
Akira Maeda.

342
00:22:25,218 --> 00:22:27,471
Yasutoshi Mori.

343
00:22:27,554 --> 00:22:29,890
1990…

344
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:33,268
'99…

345
00:22:34,394 --> 00:22:35,520
April…

346
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:37,898
"Tateishi Station, assault at restaurant."

347
00:22:38,607 --> 00:22:41,401
April 1999.

348
00:22:41,902 --> 00:22:44,696
'70… No. '85.

349
00:23:03,131 --> 00:23:06,218
"Summary of assault on manager."

350
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:08,637
"Bunko Ramen."

351
00:23:12,432 --> 00:23:13,934
Bunko Ramen.

352
00:23:14,017 --> 00:23:16,019
[music fades out]

353
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:19,689
[sighs]

354
00:23:21,525 --> 00:23:23,276
You're trying to tell me…

355
00:23:24,569 --> 00:23:26,822
that my husband was involved in this?

356
00:23:30,534 --> 00:23:32,494
I know it must be hard to hear.

357
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:37,374
Your husband's death wasn't a suicide.

358
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,043
They wanted him to pay.

359
00:23:40,836 --> 00:23:43,338
This Mufu organization silenced him.

360
00:23:45,424 --> 00:23:46,550
[Chieko] Mufu?

361
00:23:49,553 --> 00:23:50,637
[sighs]

362
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:53,932
I'm sorry, Ms. Kono,
but you must be confused.

363
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:58,186
That isn't right.

364
00:23:59,229 --> 00:24:01,481
Mufu isn't some secret cabal.

365
00:24:03,608 --> 00:24:05,193
So then what is it?

366
00:24:07,904 --> 00:24:09,698
Mufu is a band.

367
00:24:12,284 --> 00:24:14,578
My husband started a band
with a few of his friends

368
00:24:14,661 --> 00:24:16,079
when he was in high school.

369
00:24:17,873 --> 00:24:18,790
What?

370
00:24:41,396 --> 00:24:42,772
There they all are.

371
00:24:42,856 --> 00:24:45,567
MUFU

372
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:51,490
CONQUER THE WHOLE WORLD!
OTOMO, KAI, SAKAMOTO

373
00:24:53,408 --> 00:24:56,786
Do you know… the third man? It says "Kai".

374
00:24:57,329 --> 00:24:58,288
[Chieko] Kai?

375
00:24:58,830 --> 00:24:59,831
Oh, yes.

376
00:25:01,875 --> 00:25:03,376
He was the frontman.

377
00:25:04,794 --> 00:25:06,630
He doesn't look quite like that anymore.

378
00:25:09,466 --> 00:25:11,593
Anymore? You still know him, then?

379
00:25:12,719 --> 00:25:13,720
Oh, yes.

380
00:25:15,305 --> 00:25:16,598
Takeshi Miura.

381
00:25:17,557 --> 00:25:20,185
From frontman to governor.
Can you imagine?

382
00:25:20,268 --> 00:25:22,354
[mournful music playing]

383
00:25:38,954 --> 00:25:41,122
I'm so sorry for disturbing you.

384
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:42,624
[Chieko] Hmm?

385
00:25:50,090 --> 00:25:51,675
Thank you very much.

386
00:25:55,262 --> 00:25:57,847
REFORM WITHOUT WASTE TO CREATE
A NEW TOKYO - TAKESHI MIURA

387
00:25:57,931 --> 00:25:59,266
TOKYO GOVERNOR ELECTION

388
00:25:59,349 --> 00:26:00,559
[phone ringing]

389
00:26:00,642 --> 00:26:03,186
- [fax machine whirring]
- [mournful music continues]

390
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:22,455
[mournful music ends]

391
00:26:22,539 --> 00:26:23,790
[record crackling]

392
00:26:23,873 --> 00:26:26,418
["Ellie My Love"
by Southern All Stars playing]

393
00:26:30,630 --> 00:26:32,757
[Kyoko] "Your next target
is Takeshi Miura."

394
00:26:32,841 --> 00:26:35,635
"I sent his image by fax. Kill him."

395
00:26:35,719 --> 00:26:37,220
SEND

396
00:26:37,304 --> 00:26:40,890
[singing in Japanese]
♪ <i>If you still want </i>♪

397
00:26:40,974 --> 00:26:44,519
♪ <i>My affection </i>♪

398
00:26:44,603 --> 00:26:51,276
♪ <i>After I've been distant, made you cry </i>♪

399
00:26:51,359 --> 00:26:58,325
♪ <i>I'll make you my final lady </i>♪

400
00:26:58,825 --> 00:27:00,243
[in English] ♪ <i>Ellie </i>♪

401
00:27:00,327 --> 00:27:02,037
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

402
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:03,246
<i>♪ So sweet… </i>♪

403
00:27:03,330 --> 00:27:04,581
MESSAGE SENT
OK

404
00:27:05,290 --> 00:27:08,877
[in Japanese]
♪ <i>If one day our feelings fade </i>♪

405
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:12,547
♪ <i>And turn to tender sorrow </i>♪

406
00:27:12,631 --> 00:27:19,137
♪ <i>If I'm left with nothing</i>
<i>But memories of you </i>♪

407
00:27:19,679 --> 00:27:25,894
♪ <i>Once we're at a loss for words</i>
<i>Love is over </i>♪

408
00:27:26,394 --> 00:27:27,937
[in English] ♪ <i>Ellie </i>♪

409
00:27:28,021 --> 00:27:29,606
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

410
00:27:29,689 --> 00:27:33,151
<i>♪ So sweet </i>♪

411
00:27:33,777 --> 00:27:39,908
[in Japanese] ♪ <i>Smile for me, baby</i>
<i>So innocently on my mind </i>♪

412
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:46,498
♪ <i>Let yourself shine, baby</i>
<i>So lovely in your sight </i>♪

413
00:27:47,582 --> 00:27:53,880
♪ <i>The day of beckoning tears</i>
<i>Sets with the sun </i>♪

414
00:27:53,963 --> 00:27:55,757
[in English] ♪ <i>Ellie, my… </i>♪

415
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,842
[music stops]

416
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:03,723
Now, that is a damn good song.

417
00:28:05,225 --> 00:28:07,227
[automated voice]
<i>Your target is Takeshi Miura.</i>

418
00:28:07,310 --> 00:28:10,271
<i>I sent his image by fax. Kill him.</i>

419
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:18,655
Oh… You wanna tell me
why this song started playing?

420
00:28:18,738 --> 00:28:20,407
- Huh? Fuckin' tell me.
- [Kaho] Stop!

421
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:22,200
[Fujita] Please, sir! Don't hurt me…

422
00:28:22,283 --> 00:28:24,202
- [Kaho] Fujita!
- [Fujita grunts]

423
00:28:24,285 --> 00:28:26,162
- [Kaho whimpering]
- [Fujita grunting]

424
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:28,790
- [Riki] You wanna live?
- [Fujita coughing]

425
00:28:28,873 --> 00:28:32,627
Then stop begging and tell me
how the fuck I make him obey orders!

426
00:28:32,711 --> 00:28:33,753
Don't hurt her!

427
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:35,964
[man] Hey, hey, hey! Take a breath!

428
00:28:36,047 --> 00:28:38,049
[eerie music playing]

429
00:28:38,133 --> 00:28:40,427
There's no need to rush.

430
00:28:49,769 --> 00:28:52,397
Whoa.

431
00:28:54,649 --> 00:28:57,318
This is incredible.

432
00:29:21,718 --> 00:29:23,887
Take your men and wait outside.

433
00:29:25,889 --> 00:29:30,101
Are you sure, boss?
This guy might have more fight in him.

434
00:29:30,185 --> 00:29:32,270
I said get the fuck out.

435
00:29:37,317 --> 00:29:38,735
Let's go.

436
00:29:40,862 --> 00:29:42,864
[eerie music builds, then fades out]

437
00:29:51,414 --> 00:29:54,292
[Kyoko] "Kenji, where are you?
We need to talk."

438
00:29:55,794 --> 00:29:57,796
[Fujita panting]

439
00:29:59,589 --> 00:30:01,132
[Miura] I have a story for you.

440
00:30:03,426 --> 00:30:06,513
I heard it when I was traveling
in Ecuador, of all places.

441
00:30:08,139 --> 00:30:10,683
Miguel was a young Ecuadorian man,

442
00:30:11,267 --> 00:30:13,269
who worked on a coffee plantation.

443
00:30:15,730 --> 00:30:17,065
Then one day,

444
00:30:17,607 --> 00:30:19,859
the plantation's owner died.

445
00:30:20,610 --> 00:30:24,823
And Miguel was the one
who inherited the land and the plantation.

446
00:30:26,366 --> 00:30:27,909
Lucky guy.

447
00:30:29,327 --> 00:30:31,246
What do you think Miguel did next?

448
00:30:40,129 --> 00:30:41,172
He sold it.

449
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:43,883
Sold off the plantation
and much of that land,

450
00:30:43,967 --> 00:30:46,135
and built himself a mansion.

451
00:30:46,219 --> 00:30:48,930
- [tense music playing]
- And it was glorious.

452
00:30:49,430 --> 00:30:52,684
He lived a life of luxury in that mansion,
you understand?

453
00:30:55,478 --> 00:30:57,230
What he didn't know

454
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:00,358
is that his house

455
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:04,153
was built on ground
that was unsuitable for construction.

456
00:31:08,283 --> 00:31:10,743
And when the spring floods
eventually came,

457
00:31:11,244 --> 00:31:12,871
it was washed away,

458
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:15,748
and lucky Miguel right along with it.

459
00:31:17,083 --> 00:31:20,253
The soil was perfect
for producing coffee beans,

460
00:31:21,588 --> 00:31:23,715
but that's all it was good for.

461
00:31:27,218 --> 00:31:29,012
Poor lucky Miguel.

462
00:31:29,095 --> 00:31:30,346
The moral of this story

463
00:31:30,430 --> 00:31:33,641
is that it's tragic
to take advantage of something…

464
00:31:36,227 --> 00:31:38,563
without understanding its value.

465
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:45,570
So, tell me how we control him.

466
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:50,825
[Fujita breathing shakily]

467
00:31:53,077 --> 00:31:55,079
[Fujita hesitates, sniffs]

468
00:31:56,831 --> 00:31:58,625
[nervously] First… First you, uh…

469
00:32:00,501 --> 00:32:01,794
you use that.

470
00:32:02,962 --> 00:32:05,048
You play "Ellie My Love"

471
00:32:05,798 --> 00:32:07,675
on the record player over there.

472
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:09,969
And… that's it.

473
00:32:12,513 --> 00:32:14,557
He'll sort of come to life. [sniffs]

474
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:18,603
So you just… You tell him what to do.

475
00:32:20,104 --> 00:32:21,940
That's all I know. [sniffs]

476
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:26,361
I think he'll do what you say,
as long as he understands it.

477
00:32:31,115 --> 00:32:32,450
Please, I…

478
00:32:33,618 --> 00:32:35,036
- Kaho, let's go--
- [Miura] Wait.

479
00:32:35,119 --> 00:32:36,829
First things first.

480
00:32:36,913 --> 00:32:38,498
I need to try it.

481
00:32:41,042 --> 00:32:42,627
You wanna end up like Miguel?

482
00:32:47,256 --> 00:32:49,258
[music fades out]

483
00:32:50,426 --> 00:32:52,261
- [owner] Hey! Come on in.
- How you doing?

484
00:32:52,345 --> 00:32:53,388
[owner] Good, yeah.

485
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:58,434
What's the matter?
I'm right about to close.

486
00:32:58,518 --> 00:33:01,396
- You wanna eat? Grab a stool.
- No, that's all right.

487
00:33:01,479 --> 00:33:03,147
I'm with the police.

488
00:33:03,231 --> 00:33:05,108
[owner sighs] Again?

489
00:33:05,191 --> 00:33:07,068
Is this about that Human Vapor thing?

490
00:33:07,151 --> 00:33:08,903
- Shit.
- [Kenji] No, no.

491
00:33:08,987 --> 00:33:11,698
It's about Bunko Ramen, the old one.
I had a few questions.

492
00:33:11,781 --> 00:33:13,366
[owner] Man, come on…

493
00:33:13,449 --> 00:33:15,576
I don't know anything about it, okay?

494
00:33:16,786 --> 00:33:18,079
You don't know anything?

495
00:33:18,955 --> 00:33:22,083
I wasn't planning on running a ramen shop.
It was my dad's place.

496
00:33:22,625 --> 00:33:24,168
I wanted to be a manga artist.

497
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:25,336
I did a few.

498
00:33:25,420 --> 00:33:28,089
<i>Run Away! Miso Ramen Man.</i>
That was my first one.

499
00:33:28,172 --> 00:33:31,676
But everyone said it was lame
and unoriginal, so I just gave it up.

500
00:33:32,677 --> 00:33:36,472
Look, do you… know
if anyone who comes here

501
00:33:36,556 --> 00:33:39,308
was maybe a regular
when your dad ran the restaurant?

502
00:33:39,809 --> 00:33:41,436
[owner] Nah, I don't know.

503
00:33:45,356 --> 00:33:48,568
Sometimes people come in
to look at the Polaroids over there.

504
00:33:50,570 --> 00:33:53,197
My dad would post pics of customers
on the wall.

505
00:33:54,282 --> 00:33:57,160
They're not mine,
but I couldn't just throw them away,

506
00:33:57,660 --> 00:34:00,329
so I put them up.
Call it a link to the past.

507
00:34:00,830 --> 00:34:02,832
[haunting music playing]

508
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:09,130
[sighs] I'm closing up, man,
so if you're not gonna eat…

509
00:34:11,883 --> 00:34:13,968
Yeah, okay. I'll take a bowl.

510
00:34:14,677 --> 00:34:15,678
You got it.

511
00:34:16,179 --> 00:34:17,180
It's on the house.

512
00:34:27,815 --> 00:34:28,816
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

513
00:34:29,358 --> 00:34:30,902
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

514
00:34:30,985 --> 00:34:33,196
<i>- ♪ So sweet… ♪</i>
- Whoa…

515
00:34:40,286 --> 00:34:41,662
[Human Vapor] Listener,

516
00:34:43,289 --> 00:34:44,624
please,

517
00:34:45,458 --> 00:34:46,918
make a wish.

518
00:34:50,338 --> 00:34:52,548
[Miura] So now I just say my wish?

519
00:34:53,674 --> 00:34:56,302
- Yeah.
- [Miura] Wonderful.

520
00:34:56,886 --> 00:34:58,387
You two are free to go.

521
00:34:58,471 --> 00:35:01,307
<i>♪ So sweet ♪</i>

522
00:35:02,016 --> 00:35:03,559
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

523
00:35:03,643 --> 00:35:05,228
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

524
00:35:05,311 --> 00:35:07,313
<i>♪ So sweet… ♪</i>

525
00:35:07,396 --> 00:35:09,065
I got a wish for ya.

526
00:35:10,024 --> 00:35:11,234
Kill those kids.

527
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:18,199
Kaho, run!

528
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:20,284
[dramatic music playing]

529
00:35:25,581 --> 00:35:27,458
- [Kaho panting]
- Come on, hurry!

530
00:35:27,542 --> 00:35:30,211
- [man 1] I said stop!
- [man 2] Get back, you little shit!

531
00:35:31,170 --> 00:35:32,213
[man 3] Stop them!

532
00:35:32,713 --> 00:35:34,257
[man 4] What the hell? Stop!

533
00:35:34,340 --> 00:35:36,217
- [Kaho] Get off me!
- [Fujita] Son of a bitch!

534
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:38,261
[man 5] What are you doing? Get them!

535
00:35:38,344 --> 00:35:40,096
- [man 6] Huh?
- [man 7] Don't move!

536
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:47,979
[Miura laughing]

537
00:35:50,189 --> 00:35:51,566
What a vision, huh?

538
00:35:52,066 --> 00:35:53,192
- Kaito!
- Let's get 'em!

539
00:35:53,693 --> 00:35:54,735
Wait!

540
00:35:55,319 --> 00:35:56,946
They're not worth it.

541
00:35:57,989 --> 00:36:00,158
They won't survive long anyway.

542
00:36:01,075 --> 00:36:03,494
[Kaho panting]

543
00:36:06,247 --> 00:36:07,582
[Kaho shrieks]

544
00:36:07,665 --> 00:36:10,793
- [Fujita] Come on, come on…
- [Kaho] Hurry! Drive! Go, go, go!

545
00:36:10,877 --> 00:36:12,086
Hold on!

546
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:14,547
[both screaming]

547
00:36:16,424 --> 00:36:18,176
- [Fujita yells]
- Look out!

548
00:36:18,676 --> 00:36:20,303
[both screaming]

549
00:36:22,597 --> 00:36:23,514
[Fujita yells]

550
00:36:25,641 --> 00:36:28,769
- You're gonna get us both killed!
- We'll be fine! We can do this!

551
00:36:34,275 --> 00:36:36,152
[Kaho whimpering]

552
00:36:38,654 --> 00:36:40,573
[Kaho breathing anxiously]

553
00:36:43,159 --> 00:36:44,118
[tires screech]

554
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:45,620
CAR RENTAL REFUELING

555
00:36:46,204 --> 00:36:47,371
[Kaho] What are you doing?

556
00:36:48,456 --> 00:36:49,707
[Fujita grunting]

557
00:36:49,790 --> 00:36:52,293
[attendant] What the hell dude?
You got a death wish?!

558
00:36:54,337 --> 00:36:56,797
Fujita, what the hell is going on?!

559
00:36:59,133 --> 00:37:01,552
- He's… He's here! Hurry! Run!
- Come on! Come on!

560
00:37:01,636 --> 00:37:02,887
[Kaho shrieks]

561
00:37:02,970 --> 00:37:05,014
[both panting]

562
00:37:14,273 --> 00:37:16,275
- What are you… Stop!
- [Fujita grunting]

563
00:37:16,817 --> 00:37:18,736
Put me down, I can still run!

564
00:37:23,950 --> 00:37:24,909
[Kaho shrieks]

565
00:37:24,992 --> 00:37:26,535
[Kaho screaming]

566
00:37:32,291 --> 00:37:33,876
[Kaho gasping] Fujita!

567
00:37:42,551 --> 00:37:44,845
- Swim, Kaho! Get outta here! Go!
- Fujita!

568
00:37:44,929 --> 00:37:46,806
Get outta here! Go!

569
00:37:50,351 --> 00:37:52,019
- [Fujita screams]
- Fujita!

570
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:53,479
Fujita!

571
00:37:53,980 --> 00:37:55,523
[Kaho screams] No!

572
00:37:56,399 --> 00:37:57,775
Fujita! [gasps]

573
00:37:57,858 --> 00:37:58,901
No, wait!

574
00:38:06,993 --> 00:38:08,995
[Fujita choking]

575
00:38:11,706 --> 00:38:13,207
[Kaho screams] No!

576
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:15,710
No! Fujita!

577
00:38:15,793 --> 00:38:18,212
[coughing] Fujita!

578
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:20,298
[Fujita choking]

579
00:38:25,469 --> 00:38:27,638
- [music stops]
- [Kaho screams] No! No!

580
00:38:27,722 --> 00:38:30,141
[whimpering]

581
00:38:30,224 --> 00:38:32,184
[spluttering]

582
00:38:53,122 --> 00:38:55,124
[whooshing, gurgling]

583
00:39:13,851 --> 00:39:16,729
KYOKO AND REN

584
00:39:18,397 --> 00:39:20,691
[poignant music playing]

585
00:39:38,959 --> 00:39:41,379
[music distorts, fades]

586
00:39:43,589 --> 00:39:46,050
[footsteps approaching slowly]

587
00:39:48,511 --> 00:39:50,888
[poignant music resumes]

588
00:40:03,150 --> 00:40:04,568
[Kyoko sighs sadly]

589
00:40:04,652 --> 00:40:07,071
I was hoping to be the one to tell you.

590
00:40:12,243 --> 00:40:13,285
Kenji.

591
00:40:15,621 --> 00:40:17,206
You know, don't you?

592
00:40:17,289 --> 00:40:18,707
[newscaster] <i>Breaking news.</i>

593
00:40:18,791 --> 00:40:22,378
<i>The Metropolitan Police Department</i>
<i>has issued an all-points bulletin</i>

594
00:40:22,461 --> 00:40:24,463
<i>for JNT reporter Kyoko Kono,</i>

595
00:40:24,547 --> 00:40:27,383
<i>who they say is involved</i>
<i>in the Human Vapor case.</i>

596
00:40:28,759 --> 00:40:31,095
<i>A police spokesperson told press</i>
<i>earlier today</i>

597
00:40:31,178 --> 00:40:33,764
<i>that Ms. Kono</i>
<i>recently became a person of interest</i>

598
00:40:33,848 --> 00:40:35,558
<i>in the string of murders in Tokyo.</i>

599
00:40:35,641 --> 00:40:38,978
<i>They allege that the reporter</i>
<i>issued orders to the Human Vapor</i>

600
00:40:39,061 --> 00:40:41,564
<i>and incited him</i>
<i>to commit the crimes in question.</i>

601
00:40:41,647 --> 00:40:43,482
<i>Kono has been missing since yesterday,</i>

602
00:40:43,566 --> 00:40:45,359
<i>and the Metropolitan Police Department</i>

603
00:40:45,443 --> 00:40:47,736
<i>is asking the public</i>
<i>for help in locating her.</i>

604
00:40:48,863 --> 00:40:50,573
<i>The killings began earlier this month</i>

605
00:40:50,656 --> 00:40:53,367
<i>when, during an interview</i>
<i>with Ms. Kono on JNT,</i>

606
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:56,370
<i>Professor Sano was murdered</i>
<i>during a live broadcast.</i>

607
00:40:56,454 --> 00:41:01,125
<i>Since then, the list of victims</i>
<i>has increased at an alarming rate.</i>

608
00:41:01,208 --> 00:41:05,087
<i>The police remind the public that Ms. Kono</i>
<i>should be considered dangerous,</i>

609
00:41:05,171 --> 00:41:07,965
<i>and that if you see her,</i>
<i>to call the authorities.</i>

610
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:11,510
You wouldn't mind an extra slice
of <i>chashu </i>pork, would you now?

611
00:41:14,388 --> 00:41:15,264
Where'd he go?

612
00:41:15,973 --> 00:41:18,350
[dramatic, emotional music playing]

613
00:41:27,443 --> 00:41:29,778
[dramatic, emotional music continues]

614
00:41:33,365 --> 00:41:35,367
[Kaho gasping]

615
00:41:39,955 --> 00:41:41,957
[panting]

616
00:41:44,418 --> 00:41:46,420
[whimpering]

617
00:41:51,592 --> 00:41:53,010
[music softens]

618
00:41:53,093 --> 00:41:55,095
[crying]

619
00:42:02,853 --> 00:42:04,855
[panicked breathing]

620
00:42:05,606 --> 00:42:07,566
[screams]

621
00:42:13,614 --> 00:42:16,200
[dramatic music playing]
